    <briefdescription>
<para>FLASH RAMFUNC driver. This file provides a Flash firmware functions which should be executed from internal SRAM. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><simplesect kind="author"><para>MCD Application Team<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>FLASH HalfPage Programming</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>FLASH Power Down in Run mode</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</simplesect>
<verbatim>==============================================================================
                 ##### Flash RAM functions #####
==============================================================================

  *** ARM Compiler ***
  --------------------
  [..] RAM functions are defined using the toolchain options.
       Functions that are executed in RAM should reside in a separate
       source module. Using the &apos;Options for File&apos; dialog you can simply change
       the &apos;Code / Const&apos; area of a module to a memory space in physical RAM.
       Available memory areas are declared in the &apos;Target&apos; tab of the
       Options for Target&apos; dialog.

  *** ICCARM Compiler ***
  -----------------------
  [..] RAM functions are defined using a specific toolchain keyword &quot;__ramfunc&quot;.

  *** GNU Compiler ***
  --------------------
  [..] RAM functions are defined using a specific toolchain attribute
       &quot;__attribute__((section(&quot;.RamFunc&quot;)))&quot;.</verbatim></para>
